      • initConnector

        public static void initConnector​(java.lang.String apikey)
        Sets up the API connector with the API key that is provided. The connector will automatically rate limit requests as to not go over the standard limit of 3600 requests an hour.
        Parameters:
        apikey - The API key from data.gov that the connector should use for the requests

      • initConnector

        public static void initConnector​(java.lang.String apikey,
                                 boolean rateLimit)
        Sets up the API connector with the API key that is provided.
        Parameters:
        apikey - The API key from data.gov that the connector should use for the requests
        rateLimit - True to allow rate limiting or false to disable it.

      • getFoodReport

        public static FoodReport getFoodReport​(java.lang.String NDBNO)
        Gets a FoodReport object with information from a 'full' report from the USDA NDB API.
        Parameters:
        NDBNO - the ndbno of the food to get the report on. Note, the string will need 0's before the number if the number is less than 5 digits.
        Returns:
        A FoodReport object that holds all of the data from the report or null if the NDBNO does not exist

      • getSearchReport

        public static SearchReport getSearchReport​(java.lang.String searchTerms)
        Gets a SearchReport based on the search terms provided. This searches for a maximum of 50 items, sorts them by search relevance and only searches the standard reference database, not the branded food items.
        Parameters:
        searchTerms - the search terms to search with
        Returns:
        the search report

      • getSearchReport

        public static SearchReport getSearchReport​(java.lang.String searchTerms,
                                           boolean sortType)
        Gets a SearchReport based on the search terms provided. This searches for a maximum of 50 items and only searches the standard reference database, not the branded food items. The parameter sortType changes how the results are sorted, either by relevance(false) or by name(true).
        Parameters:
        searchTerms - the search terms to search with
        sortType - True, to sort by name, false to sort by relevance
        Returns:
        the search report

      • getSearchReport

        public static SearchReport getSearchReport​(java.lang.String searchTerms,
                                           boolean sortType,
                                           int maxResults)
        Gets a SearchReport based on the search terms provided. This searches only the standard reference database, not the branded food items. The parameter sortType changes how the results are sorted, either by relevance(false) or by name(true).Gets the search report. The parameter maxResults changes how many results will be returned by the search, up to a maximum of 50.
        Parameters:
        searchTerms - the search terms to search with
        sortType - True, to sort by name, false to sort by relevance
        maxResults - the maximum number of results to be returned
        Returns:
        the search report

      • getSearchReport

        public static SearchReport getSearchReport​(java.lang.String searchTerms,
                                           boolean sortType,
                                           int maxResults,
                                           boolean dataSource)
        Gets a SearchReport based on all of the parameters provided. The parameter sortType changes how the results are sorted, either by relevance(false) or by name(true).Gets the search report. The parameter maxResults changes how many results will be returned by the search, up to a maximum of 50. The parameter dataSource changes the source database to search, with either the standard food reference(false), or branded food items(true).
        Parameters:
        searchTerms - the search terms to search with
        sortType - True, to sort by name, false to sort by relevance
        maxResults - the maximum number of results to be returned
        dataSource - True, to search the branded food items database, false to search the standard food reference database.
        Returns:
        the search report
